  "direction_split": "This family is structurally BEARISH-ONLY (gate requires ribbon=BEAR + a resistance rejection). There is no call-side variant of the SAME signal to run, so a within-family C-vs-P split is undefined. The documented cross-family bull-tilt (lessons C4/C5 + confluence_real_fills_validate.py by_bias) \u2014 bull books lose less than bear books on 0DTE options because puts fight positive drift + faster theta on down-moves \u2014 is the REASON this bear-only family starts at a structural disadvantage, consistent with the negative baseline reported here.",
  "honest_verdict": "NO SHIPPABLE EDGE under doctrine, but ONE robust structural finding. Of 20 strike x stop cells (174 family signals, real fills ~2025-01..2026-05): 2 cells clear the FORMAL 4-part bar (OTM1|stop_-8pct OOS +$13.08/trade and OTM2|stop_-8pct OOS +$5.75/trade, both posQ 5/6, top5<200, n>=120) and the exit mini-sweep lifts them further (best = tp1_50 + runner 2.0x + chandelier-trailing-20%: OTM1 OOS +$41.5/trade top5 57%, OTM2 OOS +$29.1/trade 6/6 quarters top5 62%). HOWEVER BOTH FAIL OP-16 anchor-no-regression: edge_capture is NEGATIVE (OTM1 -43.9, OTM2 -35.5) and stays negative even with the best exits, because OTM puts under-capture J's near-the-money anchor WINS (4/29, 5/04) while taking full losses on the LOSS anchor days. They are also LOW-WR lottery profiles (WR 32-34%). Per OP-16 (\"edge_capture < 771 REJECTED regardless of aggregate\") and anti-pattern 2.10/L92/L104 (cheap-OTM per-trade lift is partly a denominator artifact), these are NOT shippable edges -> true_edge=0. THE REAL FINDING IS THE STOP, NOT A NEW STRIKE EDGE: the tight asymmetric -8% bear premium stop (the v15 production default) DOMINATES every wider stop at EVERY strike (e.g. ITM2 -8% -$14.2 vs ITM2 -50% -$58.5 vs ITM2 chart-only -$60.1; same monotone pattern at ATM/OTM) -- wider/chart-only stops bleed badly on this family, corroborating C2/C28. The production DEFAULT cell ITM2|stop_-8pct is -$14.2/trade overall (OOS -$8.2), CONFIRMING the prior real-fills verdict that this bear-only book is negative at the strike J actually trades. NET: do NOT flip anything live; keep bearish_rejection_morning WATCH_ONLY. The only do-no-harm note is that the -8% bear stop is already correct and wider stops would REGRESS it.",
  "op20_disclosures": {
    "authority": "real OPRA fills (C1) via simulate_trade_real \u2014 the only WR/expectancy authority",
    "realfills_window": "OPRA cache ends ~2026-05-29 (SPY260529); real fills ~2025-01-02..2026-05-29. Fires after that = no_fill. OOS(2026) real fills cover Jan-May 2026.",
    "per_trade": "expectancy (overall_per_trade / oos_per_trade) reported, not WR alone (OP-14)",
    "is_oos_split": "IS=2025, OOS=2026 (calendar). per-trade reported each side.",
    "concentration": "top5_day_pct = top-5 winning DAYS as % of net total (None when net<=0).",
    "positive_quarters": "count of calendar quarters with positive net P&L, out of quarters seen.",
    "levels": "historically-rebuilt level proxies (_detect_from_history), NOT production star/Carry named set \u2014 disclosed; placement edge is real, reaction edge unproven (L142-144).",
    "no_survivor_cherry_pick": "anti-pattern 2.10: any positive cell that is tiny-N / high-concentration / OOS-negative is marked clears_bar=false.",
    "prior_result": "stratify_bearish_rejection_quality.py (ATM+ITM2 chart-stop-only) found this book NEGATIVE (baseline ATM exp -$32.8, PSR(>0)=0.04). This sweep adds the strike x stop x exit dimension it did not explore."
  },
